message.entry: Operands to bitcmp must be numeric.
Bitcmp does not accept complex operands.
Values in A should not have \"on\" bits in positions greater than N.
The N argument to BITCMP must be a real scalar integer in the appropriate range.
Invalid data type. First argument must be integer or double.
Double inputs must have integer values in the range of ASSUMEDTYPE.
ASSUMEDTYPE must be an integer type name.
Integer inputs cannot be assumed as any other types than their own types.
BITCMP(A,N) does not accept integer valued input N. Use BITCMP(A,ASSUMEDTYPE) instead.
